flavorText: Snowy mountains are this Pokémon's habitat. During an ancient ice age, they moved to southern areas.
Its large ears are flapped like wings when it is listening to distant sounds. It extends toxic barbs when angered.
The shock waves from its cries can tip over trucks. It stamps its feet to power up.
Because it stores several kinds of toxic gases in its body, it is prone to exploding without warning.
Its flat, thin body is always stuck on walls. Its shape appears to have some meaning.
In snow, the pure white coat covering its body obscures it from predators.
Because of its ability to slip through block walls, it is said to be from another dimension.
It weakens its prey with sound waves intense enough to cause headaches, then entangles them with its sticky tongue.
It has the ability to reconstitute its entire cellular structure to transform into whatever it sees.
It has a mischievous spirit. If it spots an angler, it will tug on the fishing line to interfere.
Feared and loathed by many, it is believed to bring misfortune to all those who see it at night.
A pair may be seen rubbing their cheek pouches together in an effort to share stored electricity.
A legendary bird Pokémon that is said to appear to doomed people who are lost in icy mountains.
If anyone dares to grab its hilt, it wraps a blue cloth around that person's arm and drains that person's life energy completely.
More and more people play the slots every day, trying to win a Porygon.
It usually clings to cliffs. When it spots its prey, it spreads its wings and glides down to attack.
If it builds up enough speed swimming, it can jump out above the waves and glide for over 300 feet.
Inside the shell, it is soft and weak as it prepares to evolve. It stays motionless in the shell.
It flies straight at its target's face then clamps down on the startled victim to inject poison.
It uses black pearls to amplify its psychic power. It does a strange dance to control foes' minds.
If it is angered or startled, the fur all over its body bristles like sharp needles that pierce foes.
It bounces playfully like a ball. The more seawater it swallows, the higher it bounces.
Swallowing large amounts of water, they make snow clouds inside their bodies and, when angry, cause violent blizzards.
It pushes the tips of its two tails against the foe, then lets loose with over 20,000 volts of power.
It stuns its prey with psychokinesis and then grinds them to mush with its strong teeth. Even Shellder's shell is no match for it.
Unable to survive in hot areas, it makes itself comfortable by breathing out air cold enough to cause snow. It burrows into the snow to sleep.
It is smart enough to hunt in packs. It uses a variety of cries for communicating with others.
Deep in the jungle, high in the lofty canopy, this Pokémon abides. On rare occasions, it shows up at the beach to match wits with Slowking.
In battle, it uses its bladed tail to counter any Zangoose. It secretes a deadly venom in its tail.
They live in groups of a few individuals. Protective membranes shield their eyes from sandstorms.
Its swimming form is exquisitely elegant. With its thin mouth, it feeds on seaweed that grows between rocks.
It is said to have emerged from an egg in a place where there was nothing, then shaped the world.
They pretend to be elaborate coffins to teach lessons to grave robbers. Their bodies are covered in pure gold.
A highly intelligent Pokémon. By folding back its wings in flight, it can overtake jet planes.
Because of the way it floats aimlessly, an old folktale calls it a "Signpost for Wandering Spirits."
Its cells are all magnetic, and it communicates with others by using magnetic pulses.
It electrifies its claws and tears its opponents apart with them. Even if they dodge its attack, they'll be electrocuted by the flying sparks.
In the distant past, it was stronger than its horribly weak descendants that exist today.
Its body is said to be harder than any kind of metal. A study has revealed that its body is hollow.
It creates barriers from electrified silk that stun foes. This works as a weapon as well as a defense.
Starlight is the source of their power. At night, they mark star positions by using psychic power to float stones.
It is actually three Magnemite linked by magnetism. A group can set off a magnetic storm.
It can loose 100,000-volt bursts of electricity, instantly downing foes several times its size.
It is said that each of its nine tails contains a different magical power.
Its petals are the largest in the world. As it walks, it scatters extremely allergenic pollen.
It has slept underground for hundreds of millions of years since its birth. It's occasionally found during the excavation of caves.
Although its fur has many admirers, it is tough to raise as a pet because of its fickle meanness.
Lives about one yard underground where it feeds on plant roots. It sometimes appears aboveground.
There are some places where Slowpoke is worshiped because of a long-standing belief that whenever Slowpoke yawns, it rains.
It uses black pearls to amplify its psychic power. It does a strange dance to control foes' minds.
It has a very fine fur. Take care not to make it angry, or it may inflate steadily and hit with a Body Slam.
They employ an electrically charged web to trap their prey. While it is immobilized by shock, they leisurely consume it.
Dreaming of one day flying, it practices by leaping off cliffs every day.
Born from temperatures and pressures deep underground, it fires beams from the stone in its head.
A mythical Pokémon said to have swelled the seas with rain and tidal waves. It battled with Groudon.
If its Trainer becomes happy, it overflows with energy, dancing joyously while spinning about.
Unsanitary places are what they like best. They can be spotted in Alola, often with Grimer in hot pursuit.
It is easily angered. By swinging its well-developed horn wildly, it can even punch through diamond.
When it shares the infinite energy it creates, that being's entire body will be overflowing with power.
It is always outrageously furious. If it gives chase, it will tenaciously track the target no matter how far.
This Pokémon is fully covered by nonflammable fur. It can withstand any kind of fire attack.
It feeds on soil. After it has eaten a large mountain, it will fall asleep so it can grow.
This Pokémon flashes a bright light that blinds its prey. This creates an opening for it to deliver an electrical attack.
Its claws loose electricity with enough amperage to cause fainting. They live in small groups.
No two Spinda have the same pattern of spots. Its tottering step fouls the aim of foes.
Loves to build its muscles. It trains in all styles of martial arts to become even stronger.
With their sucker mouths, they suck in prey. Then they use their fangs to shock the prey with electricity.
Research is progressing on storing lightning in Electabuzz so this energy can be used at any time.
Its body temperature is roughly 18,000 degrees F. Flames spout from gaps in its hardened shell.
Its jaws are terrifyingly powerful. It could eat Omastar and Omanyte whole and not be bothered in the slightest by their shells.
It is born asleep, and it dies asleep. All its movements are apparently no more than the results of it tossing and turning in its dreams.
It is highly attuned to the emotions of people and Pokémon. It hides if it senses hostility.
It discovers what is going on around it by using the feelers on its head and tail. It is brutally aggressive.
It is recognized by its rock-hard hide and its extended horn. Be careful with the horn as it contains venom.
The combination of garbage bags and industrial waste caused the chemical reaction that created this Pokémon.
A sea of fire engulfs the surroundings of their battles, since they use their six wings to scatter their ember scales.
In battle, it digs through the ground and strikes the unsuspecting foe from an unexpected direction.
Uses anti-gravity to stay suspended. Appears without warning and uses attacks like Thunder Wave.
If the Shellder attached to its tail becomes separated, this Pokémon reverts to a normal Slowpoke.
When the bulb on its back grows large, the Pokémon seems to lose the ability to stand on its hind legs.
Beware the poisonous liquid it shoots from its right arm. If even a little of it gets on you, you'll experience the effects of the unidentified toxin.
Always furious and tenacious to boot. It will not abandon chasing its quarry until its quarry is caught.
Very lazy. Just eats and sleeps. As its rotund bulk builds, it becomes steadily more slothful.

It stores static electricity in its fur for discharging. It gives off sparks if a storm approaches.
They set off on their own from their pride and live by themselves to become stronger. These hot-blooded Pokémon are quick to fight.
Wherever Grimer has passed, so many germs are left behind that no plants will ever grow again.
The biggest of all Pokémon. It can dive to a depth of almost 10,000 feet on only one breath.
A Pokémon ancestor that was reanimated from a fossil. It lived in the sea and hunted with claws.
These key collectors threaten any attackers by fiercely jingling their keys at them.
The spiny fur on its back is normally at rest. When this Pokémon becomes agitated, its fur stands on end and stabs into its attackers.
Its body is gaseous and frail. It slowly grows as it collects dust from the atmosphere.
It is born deep underground. It can't emerge until it has entirely consumed the soil around it.
Starry skies thousands of light-years away are visible in the space distorted by their intense psychic power.
It does not need eyes, because it emits ultrasonic waves to check its surrounding while it flies.
Its sturdy legs give it sure footing, even in mud. It burrows into dirt to sleep.
When Vaporeon's fins begin to vibrate, it is a sign that rain will come within a few hours.
It's thought to be monitoring the ecosystem. There are rumors that even greater power lies hidden within it.
A legendary Pokémon that is said to live in thunderclouds. It freely controls lightning bolts.
Its feet have suction cups designed to stick to any surface. It tenaciously climbs trees to forage.
It is formed by two Beldum joining together. Its two brains are linked, amplifying its psychic power.
All of its fur dazzles if danger is sensed. It flees while the foe is momentarily blinded.
Apparently, it cracked Shellder's shell with its sharp fangs and sucked out the insides.
It protects its skin by covering its body in delicate bubbles. Beneath its happy-go-lucky air, it keeps a watchful eye on its surroundings.
When DODUO evolves into this odd breed, one of its heads splits into two. It runs at nearly 40 mph.
By drinking pure water, it grows its icy body. This Pokémon can be hard to find on days with warm, sunny weather.
Its body is composed of plasma. It is known to infiltrate electronic devices and wreak havoc.
Generations have believed that any wish written on a note on its head will come true when it awakens.
Its magnetic nose consistently faces north. Travelers check Nosepass to get their bearings.
It is actually three Magnemite linked by magnetism. A group can set off a magnetic storm.
On nights around the quarter moon, the aurora from its tail extends and undulates beautifully.
It uses the sucker on its head to hang from a tree or from eaves. It can produce seven different tones.
While lulling its enemies with its vacant look, this wily Pokémon will use psychokinetic powers.
It observes prey while hanging inverted from branches. When the chance presents itself, it swoops!
It has a mischievous spirit. If it spots an angler, it will tug on the fishing line to interfere.
Spacing out is basically all it does. It turns back into Slowpoke if its tail, along with Shellder, breaks off.
Munna always float in the air. People whose dreams are eaten by them forget what the dreams had been about.
It is doused with mushroom spores when it is born. As its body grows, mushrooms sprout from its back.
Be careful if it turns its back during battle. It means that it will attack with the fire on its back.
It is nearly impossible to parry its attacking scythes. Its movements are like a ninja's.
They are born in snow clouds. They use chains made of ice crystals to capture prey.
They intently observe both Trainers and Pokémon. Apparently, they are looking at something that only Gothita can see.
It is said that kids who drink MILTANK's milk grow up to become hearty, healthy adults.
It doesn't like to be taken care of. It's difficult to bond with since it won't listen to its Trainer.
MACHOKE's boundless power is very dangerous, so it wears a belt that suppresses its energy.
If its horns capture the warm feelings of people or Pokémon, its body warms up slightly.
Its swimming form is exquisitely elegant. With its thin mouth, it feeds on seaweed that grows between rocks.
The instant it presses the tips of its tails onto an opponent, it sends over 20,000 volts of electricity into the foe.
The vibrating of the bumps all over its body causes earthquake-like tremors. Seismitoad and Croagunk are similar species.
It picks food from cactus plants, deftly avoiding buds and spines. It seems to skip about to move.
The heavy control mask it wears suppresses its intrinsic capabilities. This Pokémon has some hidden special power.
Its skin has a rubbery elasticity, so it can reduce damage by defensively pulling it skin up to its neck.
Its hard shell repels any kind of attack. It is vulnerable only when its shell is open.

The flames it breathes when angry contain toxins. If they cause a burn, it will hurt forever.
It lives in forests and fields. Squabbles over territory occur when flocks collide.
It has volcanoes on its back. If magma builds up in its body, it shudders, then erupts violently.
Its ear is hexagonal in shape. Compressed underground, its body is as hard as steel.
It dislikes cold places, so it blows scorching flames to make the environment suitable for itself.
If its Trainer becomes happy, it overflows with energy, dancing joyously while spinning about.
A poisonous bite reacted with its system, blessing it with the enhanced intellect of a genius. It has full control of its psychic powers.
There are researchers who believe this Pokémon reflected like a mirror in the distant past.
It discharges electricity from its mane. It creates a thundercloud overhead to drop lightning bolts.
With four linked brains, it's more intelligent than a supercomputer, and it uses calculations to analyze foes.
Even though it is filled with acid, it does not melt because it also oozes a protective fluid.
The swirl on its belly undulates. Staring at it may gradually cause drowsiness.
It has always been supposed that Seel live only in cold seas. Their having shown up in Alola is a mystery.
Protected by a hard shell, it spins its body like a wheel and crashes furiously into its enemies.
It lives alone, away from others. Apparently, every one of them believes it is the most important.
When its anger reaches a breaking point, this Pokémon unleashes a fierce blizzard that freezes every creature around it, be they friend or foe.
To protect itself, it afflicts those around it with nightmares. However, it means no harm.
It digs into the ground with its tail and makes a mazelike nest. It can fly just a little.
The mist emanating from their foreheads is packed with the dreams of people and Pokémon.
Although small, its venomous barbs render this Pokémon dangerous. The female has smaller horns.

When scared, this Pokémon cries. Its tears pack the chemical punch of 100 onions, and attackers won't be able to resist weeping.
It is vulnerable to attack because its shell is soft, exposing its weak and tender body.
Its body always burns with an orange glow that enables it to hide perfectly among flames.
This odd Pokémon can see both the past and the future. It eyes the sun's movement all day.
If its fins being to vibrate, it is a sign that it will begin raining soon.
